<subSubSection pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="118.[189,454,1311,1337]" box="[189,454,1311,1337]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,1311,1337]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,1311,1337]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="118.[188,1399,1358,1697]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,537,1358,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weiperti" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[189,300,1358,1384]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[315,426,1358,1384]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Cheilosia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[442,537,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">weiperti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[542,630,1358,1384]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a slender, comparatively short species, with moderately long and dense pilosity, with a typical structure shared by taxa of 
<taxonomicName box="[837,941,1393,1419]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Cheilosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[837,941,1393,1419]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Cheilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[948,1008,1393,1419]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
of the distiphallus (apical sclerite of the aedeagus-complex). 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[512,783,1427,1454]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weiperti" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[512,624,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[642,669,1428,1454]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[687,783,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">weiperti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[792,884,1428,1454]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from all species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[1207,1319,1427,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1207,1319,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by set of the following characters: face protruded with facial tubercle in lower part, facial tubercle of distinct shape, scutellum with long, black, bristle-like pile (much longer than length of scutellum), antennae black, mesonotum black, fore coxa without baso-lateral spur. The species has a very pronounced sexual dimorphism, especially in colour of the legs. A similar shape of face, wing venation, and occurrence of males and females simultaneously at the same locality lends support to their conspecificity. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weiperti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Cheilosia weiperti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[289,376,1637,1663]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Cheng, 2004" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2004" box="[579,1003,1636,1663]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suspecta">
<emphasis box="[579,710,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">C. suspecta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y." box="[716,1003,1636,1663]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" pagination="267 - 416" refId="ref48566" refString="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y. 2004. Revision of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera: Syrphidae) of China. Contributions on Entomology International 5: 267 - 416." type="journal article" year="2004">Barkalov &amp; Cheng, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1017,1101,1636,1662]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="113.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1294,601,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-117@113.[189,1398,566,1858]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="Fig. 62. Cheilosia (Cheilosia) suspecta Barkalov &amp; Cheng, 2004. A. Male head, lateral view. B. Female head, anterior view. C. Aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. D. Superior lobe of hypandrium, lateral view. E. Basoflagellomere, lateral view. F. Tip of wing. G. Surstylus and gonocercus, lateral view. After Barkalov &amp; Cheng 2004. Scale bars indicated in drawings." pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
), and can be differentiated by characteristic shape of superior lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="118.[189,324,1737,1763]" box="[189,324,1737,1763]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1737,1763]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1737,1763]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="118.[189,1398,1783,1844]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
The species is named after and in honour of Dr Jörg Weipert (Plaue, 
<collectingCountry box="[1050,1167,1783,1809]" name="Germany" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Germany</collectingCountry>
), who collected an impressive amount of 
<taxonomicName box="[450,619,1817,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[450,562,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Cheilosia</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[656,726,1817,1843]" name="Nepal" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and allowed us to study the material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
